Durban - A 30-year-old man has been arrested and charged for the murder of a 22-year-old Hillcrest woman. According to KZN police spokesman, Colonel Thembeka Mbele, it is alleged that a domestic dispute took place between the couple at around 1 am on Wednesday morning at Winston Park. "It is alleged that a 22-year-old woman stabbed the 30-year-old man on the stomach. "The suspect took a brick and assaulted the victim on the head. The victim was declared dead at the scene by paramedics." Mbele said the 30-year-old man was treated on scene by paramedics and is expected to appear in court shortly. ER24 spokesman,Russel Meiring, said when paramedics arrived on scene the woman was lying on the floor in a pool of blood. Meiring said she had sustained a serious head wound and there was nothing paramedics could do for her and she was declared dead on scene. DAILY NEWS  